        "timestamp": "2018-01-16 08:09:09.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe GVNFM use tosca-nfv-v1.0-wd04-rev04 profile. It is not a bug.\nFor the ONAP VNF TOSCA profile is not defined yet. After model subcommittee defined, we will consider how to support it.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "0a9e65d382adb5eec5deb1ce11de0a1f025e2b20",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2255,
          "name": "Dénes Németh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "denes.nemeth@nokia.com",
          "username": "thelittlemouse"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-01-16 09:52:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nWhen any of the  sample VOLTE R1 package (https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/VOLTE+test+case+input+collection+for+tracking) is uploaded to ONAP it is transformed by ONAP an if the package is downloaded from VF-C catalog the transformed package has the tosca_definitions_version: tosca_simple_yaml_1_1\nmetadata:\n  resourceVendorRelease: 1.0.0.wd03\nversions. I am not sure where the problem is . Please see attachments to the JIRA bug.\n > The GVNFM use tosca-nfv-v1.0-wd04-rev04 profile. It is not a bug.\n > For the ONAP VNF TOSCA profile is not defined yet. After model\n > subcommittee defined, we will consider how to support it.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "66349dec2ca82c803f50fee558215d64626f5828",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 141,
          "name": "maopeng zhang",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "zhang.maopeng1@zte.com.cn",
          "username": "maopengzhang"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-02-11 05:59:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n1. in R1, VNFD is not standard in ONAP community, only VNF package structure is standard; What you provided is from the VNF vendors, which is not accepted by the model subcommittee. \n2. Also in R1, VFC do not parse the VNF vendor's package and make it as blackbox\n3. The GVNFM will use the VNFD as I said\n4. In my code review ,what you change is not complete as well.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
